  "texts": [
    "This approach captures explicit gendered language in self-descriptions while preserving cases where models reference multiple people or relationships.",
    "M.2 ResultsOverall, 87.8% of responses (11,235/12,800) used gender-neutral language when maintaining professional personas.",
    "Gendered language usage varied substantially by persona, ranging from 1.8% (Financial Advisor) to 19.4% (Classical Musician).",
    "This represents a 10.5-fold difference (Table 12).",
    "M.3 Interpretation: Domain-Specific Patterns Suggest Training EffectsThree personas showed gendered language rates between 11-19%: Classical Musician (19.4%), Small Business Owner (16.6%), and Neurosurgeon (11.0%)."
  ]
